elements.2211.03294_0b99a3c0cd076f9bafdf1d1d151b8: We propose a simple model comprising three particles to study the nonlinear mechanical response of jammed frictional granular materials under oscillatory shear
elements.2211.03294_20237e28000c51cb24aa6844afe19: Owing to the introduction of the simple model, we obtain an exact analytical expression of the complex shear modulus for a system including many monodispersed disks, which satisfies a scaling law in the vicinity of the jamming point
elements.2211.03294_6b3c4e166326ad4d1599e37878c77: These expressions perfectly reproduce the shear modulus of the many-body system with low strain amplitudes and friction coefficients
elements.2211.03294_d11a66d4905c7ff28523b8d92984d: Even for disordered many-body systems, the model reproduces results by introducing a single fitting parameter.

elements.2211.03294_06adc61cb2f2ba494bc4da73bd1b8: The theoretical analysis of densely dispersed grains is challenging as a typical many-body problem in non-equilibrium systems
elements.2211.03294_085a8236a125253e1008fa436197e: To date, a few theoretical approaches have been proposed for systems related to frictionless particles
elements.2211.03294_6cdd1b36ff34ba733b9087fff8200: The scaling laws for the linear elastic response were derived in terms of the vibrational density of states
elements.2211.03294_ab63462b0c3d1047b22959f31b38b: The Fourier analysis of particle trajectories helps generate semi-analytical expressions for
elements.2211.03294_2bdfea5888bea38eea65f34e656f3: Unfortunately, these theories can not apply to frictional particles because of the history-dependent contact force
elements.2211.03294_b1a261b145ac10e697f77e6c6896b: It is helpful to analyze a simple model with small degrees of freedom to understand the behavior of many-body systems, including densely dispersed grains
elements.2211.03294_d3b3696fb4762ecf16b5d7d7f0b30: This approach has been used in statistical mechanics
elements.2211.03294_78ab6e6ce7c7e763626d682dabea8: The mean-field approximation of the Ising model is a typical example in which the system contains only one Ising spin under the influence of a self-consistently determined mean field
elements.2211.03294_75880f3cf9b6167dfc0ad7144c890: For atomic liquids, a cell model, in which a single atom exists in a cage, was used to derive the equation of state
elements.2211.03294_12a4b94b396ab7c406b829000c6da: The coherent potential approximation for disordered solids has been used to understand electronic band structures
elements.2211.03294_2c1b4755949d449f9947fe170354d: The effective medium theory reveals the elastic response of random spring networks
elements.2211.03294_ede6ea880fe80f404ce393d4aa100: In addition, a simple model consisting of two particles was proposed to reproduce the liquid-solid phase transition
elements.2211.03294_6b7c7b15bd194a321bf1ac30ad984: The advantage of such few-body models is that we can obtain exact solutions
elements.2211.03294_61c9bd43fbb2f839566089f8537b6: The qualitative behavior of the corresponding many-body systems can be determined based on the solutions of the few-body models
elements.2211.03294_4f95a2d0c2f40f356b0750ad72c62: Thus, we adopt this approach to determine the nonlinear responses of the frictional dispersed grains
elements.2211.03294_2f9d7858e8115f0854205950bb849: This study proposes a model consisting of three identical particles to describe the mechanical response of jammed frictional granular materials under oscillatory shear
elements.2211.03294_ab71383fdc6d9a5d14568c54352a6: We demonstrate that the model reproduces the storage and loss moduli of many-particle systems (MPSs) without any fitting parameter if there is no disorder in the particle configuration
elements.2211.03294_3f95b51ac73919e0039b071efc260: This model can be analytically solved for low-strain amplitudes and friction coefficients near the jamming point.
elements.2211.03294_60dfe9b5a9a7e913963391f298f74: We derive a scaling law for the complex shear modulus, which semi-quantitatively agrees with the numerical simulations of the MPS even if disorder exists with the introduction of a fitting parameter.
